#note cool, I thought CAEOMA was a no-brainer, but there's a better play - OHMAGE at 12J. I sacrifice 15 points, but given the game situation I most likely need to bingo to win, and OHMAGE opens up two great lanes (to the G and the E) and also keeps a stronger leave. Not sure that I ever would've come up with that move over the board.
>Joanne_Craig: ABDENNT J1 EN +23 371
